502-504 East 118th Street, south side, just east of Pleasant avenue. No. 502 is a 2-1/2 story frame house.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 250

(1)
East 118th Street, north side, east from (No. 517), but not including Pleasant Ave., to the Harlem River. Notice building on Randall's Island in the background.
September 12, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, and showing a closer view of Nos. 517 to 529.
July 16, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
